 interlocking issues of affect, affinity, accessibility, and activism in the context of this tradition. Juxtaposing book history; reading practices; literary analysis; feminist criticism; and communication, religious, political, and cultural studies; the contributors map a range of possibilities for further research on Oprah's Book Club. A complete chronological list of Book Club picks is included.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBook clubs (Discussion groups)zUnited States. 0aOprah Winfrey show (Television program). 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh1 aAubry, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Kimberly Chabot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDouglas, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarr, Cecilia Konchar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarker, Jaime, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarker, Jaime, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKonchar Farr, Cecilia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLewis, Kelley Penfield, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLofton, Kathryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerry, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuirk, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRodríguez, Ana Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https:/